parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument cluster can cause inaccurate and erratic readings of vital vehicle information, such as speed, temperature, and fuel levels, which can lead to confusion, accidents, or engine damage.
symptoms: Speedometer
tachometer
gas gauge
and heat gauge readings are inaccurate or erratic
speedometer reads incorrectly while at a complete stop
temperature gauge reads overheating soon after starting the engine
instrument panel goes out or becomes unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause engine stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loose battery cable nut
interference with high-ampereage equipment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump wiring harness can cause the fuel pump to malfunction, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially, a fire hazard, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The fuel pump fails to work
the engine stalls or loses power
the wires inside the fuel tank burn out
the wires become hot and melt the plastic insulation
the fuel pump wiring harness shows signs of melting or burning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without input from the driver
the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly
the vehicle's idle speed fluctuates erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning cruise control can cause driver distraction, loss of vehicle control, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control does not engage properly
the cruise control disengages unexpectedly
the vehicle requires the engine to be turned off and on to reset the cruise control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold bolts can cause exhaust gases to leak into the vehicle, posing a significant risk to the health and safety of occupants.
symptoms: Broken or loose exhaust manifold bolts
exhaust gases leaking into the vehicle
poor fitting manifolds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel horn can delay or prevent the sounding of the horn in emergency situations, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty sounding the horn
requiring excessive force to sound the horn
delayed or no response to horn activation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auxiliary power stud can cause a loss of power, leading to accidents, and in some cases, fires.
symptoms: Loss of power while driving
deformed support assembly
fires starting under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the vehicle without warning can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling without indication
gas cap replacement
fuel pump replacement
burning wires.
